exports[`Functions — core formatting > noop (minimal) 1`] = `
"# noop()

> **noop**(): \`void\`

A function that does nothing and returns undefined.

Useful as a default callback or placeholder.


---

## Returns: \`void\`

Always returns \`undefined\`.

---

## Since

2.0.0

---

## Also known as

<AlsoKnownAs data={{"lodash":{"name":"noop","group":"Util"},"ramda":{"name":"always","group":"Function"},"radashi":{"name":"noop","group":"Function"},"remeda":{"name":"doNothing","group":"Function"},"moderndash":null,"antfu":{"name":"noop","group":"function"},"effect":{"name":"constVoid","group":"Function"},"es-toolkit":{"name":"noop","group":"function"},"python":null,"kotlin":null}} />


---

## Example

\`\`\`typescript
// Default callback to avoid null checks
function fetchData(onSuccess: () => void = noop) {
  // No need for: if (onSuccess) onSuccess()
  onSuccess();
}

// In tests
const handler: Arrayable<() => void> = [noop, noop];
expect(processItems(handler)).toHaveLength(2);
\`\`\`

---

## How it works?

A function that does nothing and returns \`undefined\`.
<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
