exports[`Functions — taphos (lodash compat) > add (taphos, math) 1`] = `
"# ~~add()~~

> **add**(\`augend\`, \`addend\`): \`number\`

Adds two numbers.

:::warning DEPRECATED

Use the \`+\` operator directly instead.

:::


---

## Parameters

### augend: \`number\`

The first number in an addition.

### addend: \`number\`

The second number in an addition.

---

## Returns: \`number\`

The sum.


---

## See Also

[Addition (+) - MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Addition)

---

## Since

2.0.0

---

## Also known as

<AlsoKnownAs data={{"lodash":{"name":"add","group":"Math"},"ramda":{"name":"add","group":"Math"},"radashi":null,"remeda":null,"moderndash":null,"antfu":null,"effect":null,"es-toolkit":null,"python":{"name":"+","group":"builtins"},"kotlin":{"name":"+","group":"kotlin"}}} />


---

## Example

\`\`\`typescript
// ❌ Deprecated approach
add(6, 4);   // => 10

// ✅ Recommended approach
6 + 4;       // => 10
\`\`\`

---

## How it works?

Adds two numbers.
**Deprecated**: Use the \`+\` operator directly.
<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
    A["add(6, 4)"] --> B["10"]\`}
  mobile={\`flowchart TB
    A["add(6, 4)"] --> B["10"]\`}
/>

### Native Equivalent

\`\`\`typescript
// ❌ add(6, 4)
// ✅ 6 + 4
\`\`\`

---

## Use Cases

### Add numbers 📌

